"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389379","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The Department is assessing the quality of the clearance time data at lower geographical levels and is considering the future release of such information into the public domain. These statistics will be published when they are ready, with the release pre-announced in line with United Kingdom Statistics Authority release protocols.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T14:56:02.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389379/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389379/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Personal Independence Payment: Bristol South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Bristol South constituency have waited longer than six months for the final outcome of their personal independent payment application.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","6728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389380","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21","<p /> <p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill on 20th July. A link to the impact assessment on the <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/" target="_blank">www.parliament.uk</a> website is included.</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006.pdf</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","6709 ; 6710","2015-07-21T16:20:55.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389380/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389380/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to section 96A(3)(b) of the Welfare Reform Act 2012 which it is proposed will be inserted by Clause 8 of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill, how he plans to identify the matters which are relevant to setting the level of the benefit cap.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","6706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389382","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions takes seriously any declarations of intention to attempt suicide or self harm that are made by its customers. There is a clear, detailed action plan that staff and contractors must follow if a customer declares an intention to kill or harm him or herself. DWP also provides guidance to help deal with these incidents.</p><p> </p><p>I have arranged for a copy of DWP’s guidance “Managing Customer Declarations of Intention to Attempt Suicide or Self Harm” to be put in the Library.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-16T16:18:21.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389382/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389382/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what guidance is provided for staff (a) working for and (b) contracted by his Department on dealing with clients who are or may be suicidal; and if he will place a copy of such guidance in the Library.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","6804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389385","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T16:04:08.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389385/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389385/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of jobseeker's allowance claims took (a) 10 days or fewer, (b) between 11 and 16 days inclusive and (c) over 16 days to process in (i) Nottingham North constituency, (ii) Nottingham local authority area and (iii) Great Britain in each financial year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","6767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389387","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20"," <p /> <p>The information is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T13:32:58.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389387/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389387/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Employment and Support Allowance: South Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in (a) Barnsley East constituency, (b) Barnsley and (c) South Yorkshire have claimed the enhanced disability premium component of employment support allowance in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","6848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389388","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>The information requested for all those placed into employment from the Work Programme, is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The information available is the number of Work Programme Referrals, Attachments and Job Outcomes, by various geographies and this can be found at:</p><p><a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T16:57:01.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389388/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389388/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Work Programme: South Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were enrolled on the Work Programme in (a) Barnsley East constituency, (b) Barnsley and (c) South Yorkshire in each of the last five years; and how many such people found employment through that Programme.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","6847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389389","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>Centre for Health and Disability Assessments is working closely with the Department to achieve all its performance requirements and progress is being made on reducing the volume of outstanding cases and reducing the time people have to wait for an assessment.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T16:42:32.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389389/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389389/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Employment and Support Allowance: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment has been made of the adequacy of employment and support allowance assessment waiting times in Wales.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389390","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>The information available for the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants by phase of claim, by parliamentary constituency, local authority and Great Britain is published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development in Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm</a></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T16:50:23.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389390/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389390/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the number of outstanding employment and support allowance assessments in (a) the UK, (b) Wales and (c) Caerphilly County Borough.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389393","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Cases are not generally given priority over any other except where the claimant is terminally ill.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-16T10:35:13.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389393/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389393/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the number of priority employment and support allowance cases in (a) the UK, (b) Wales and (c) Caerphilly County Borough.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389394","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p>The Department intends to publish out-of-work benefits mortality statistics and the publication date will be pre-announced at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/list-of-scheduled-upcoming-ad-hoc-statistical-releases" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/list-of-scheduled-upcoming-ad-hoc-statistical-releases</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","6682","2015-07-16T14:53:50.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389394/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389394/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Social Security Benefits: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the contribution of the 24 June 2015, Official Report, columns 885-86, when his Department will publish statistics on the deaths of people declared fit for work since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","6821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389395","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>The information available for the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants by phase of claim, by parliamentary constituency, local authority and Great Britain is published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development in Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm</a></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T16:54:13.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389395/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389395/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of progress in clearing the backlog of employment and support allowance assessments in (a) the UK, (b) Wales and (c) Caerphilly County Borough.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389396","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21","<p /> <p>The exact information requested is not available. Most people leave Jobseeker’s Allowance very quickly; Of those making a new JSA claim around a third leave within a month, two-thirds within three months and over eighty per cent within six months. A destinations survey in 2011 found that 70% of people leaving JSA did so because they had found work and, of those, three quarters were in employment 7-8 months later.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","6829 ; 6830","2015-07-21T12:58:29.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389396/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389396/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Jobcentre Plus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who gained employment through Jobcentre Plus between 2005 and 2015 were again unemployed after (a) eight months and (b) a year.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389398","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Department does not operate a target regime. The effectiveness of all Jobcentres is monitored by a range of measures. The Department regularly publishes information on a number of key areas of performance; these are included in our Transparency Indicators page, Statistical publications, the DWP tabulation tool and the DWP Annual Reports and Accounts. (links below for ease of reference).</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-business-plan-transparency-measures/dwp-business-plan-transparency-measures" target="_blank">DWP-business-plan-transparency-measures</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dwp-statistical-summaries-2015" target="_blank">DWP statistical summaries 2015 - Publications - GOV.UK</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/445950/dwp-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015.pdf" target="_blank">DWP annual report and accounts 2014 to 2015 - Publications - GOV.UK</a></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","6835","2015-07-21T16:44:52.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389398/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389398/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-13","Jobcentre Plus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what targets his Department has set for Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","6832"
