"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388897","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The £10 million fund will provide support for ultrafast broadband in the South West, to improve connectivity in that part of the UK.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:12:33.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388897/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388897/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Broadband: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to paragraph 1.318, of Summer Budget 2015, to what ends the Government plans to spend the £10 million for broadband in addition to the existing rural rollout programme.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388898","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The number of public buildings which have received Wi-Fi in each of the Super Connected cities is listed in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>City</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Buildings</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aberdeen</p></td><td><p>31</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belfast</p></td><td><p>91</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Birmingham</p></td><td><p>192</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Brighton and Hove</p></td><td><p>47</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridge</p></td><td><p>64</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cardiff</p></td><td><p>150</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Derby</p></td><td><p>39</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Derry/Londonderry</p></td><td><p>53</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Edinburgh</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Leeds-Bradford</p></td><td><p>147</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manchester</p></td><td><p>123</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newcastle</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newport</p></td><td><p>43</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oxford</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Perth</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Portsmouth</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Salford</p></td><td><p>84</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>York</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p><strong>1361</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:20:47.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388898/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388898/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Public Buildings: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many public buildings have been provided with free public wifi in each of the super-connected cities.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388899","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The rollout of superfast broadband is on track and an excellent progress has been made, 40,000 premises are being connected each week. To date £780m has been allocated from the TV licence fee ​to support ​the roll out of superfast ​broadband ​to 95% of homes and businesses in the UK by the end of 2017.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:06:24.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388899/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388899/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Broadband: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what forecast he has made of how much of the BBC licence fee will be allocated to broadband rollout by the end of that rollout.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388900","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The rollout of superfast broadband is on track and an excellent progress has been made. The Government is committed to achieving 95% coverage of homes and businesses in the UK by the end of 2017. Funding from the TV licence fee has been allocated to support delivery of superfast broadband to premises which would not otherwise have had coverage. It will also support delivery of the government's commitment to ensure that all premises have access to basic broadband with speeds of at least 2Mbps by the end of 2015.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:04:24.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388900/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388900/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether any of the BBC's funding for rural broadband rollout has been allocated to extending superfast broadband to households without such broadband.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388901","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-21","<p>The funding for the innovation fund which was created in order to explore ways to take superfast broadband to hardest to reach places was allocated by the Exchequer, not from the BBC’s funding for broadband.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-21T16:46:33.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388901/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388901/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Broadband: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department's innovation fund was funded from the BBC's funding for broadband.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388902","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>My Department received a total of 153 responses to the consultation on the reform of the Electronic Communications Code. My officials are currently analysing these responses and I will respond in due course. The Government remains committed to delivering a reformed Code that is clear and fit for purpose, and support UK networks to provide consumers with a choice of high quality telecommunications services.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:02:10.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388902/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388902/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential benefits of reforming the Electronic Communications Code to grant mobile network operators enhanced rights to share sites to improve mobile voice and data coverage.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","6370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388903","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>Consultation on the reform of the Code closed on 30 April 2015. I currently have my officials analysing all of the responses and we will publish a response in due course. The Government aims to reform the current Code to promote network connectivity, expand coverage and take into account the legitimate interests of all parties.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:00:32.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388903/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388903/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Mobile Phones: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what reforms to the Electronic Communications Code his Department is proposing to improve the ability of mobile network operators to increase mobile voice and data coverage in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","6371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388904","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>A copy of the list of libraries without WiFi, referred to in Question HC5223 on 6 July, will be placed in the Library before the House rises for the summer recess.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:13:31.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388904/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388904/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Public Libraries: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July 2015 to Question 5223, on public libraries: wifi, if he will place the list referred to in that Answer in the Library before the House rises for the summer recess.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388905","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>With Government's support, 95% of the country will have superfast broadband by the end of 2017. We are taking a detailed look at the impact of options to ensure that no one is left behind - including the feasibility of a broadband Universal Service Obligation. If the Government chooses to pursue this option, following public consultation, it will be for Ofcom to designate the provider or providers.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:14:37.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388905/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388905/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2015 to Question 2033, what estimate his Department has made of the number of companies that would be affected by raising the universal service obligation to 5 mbps; and what the names of those companies are.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388906","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>No discussions have been held by this Department with local authorities on business rates relief for local newspapers.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:16:47.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388906/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388906/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Local Press: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with local authorities on business rates relief for local newspapers.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388907","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>Government supports the plans for a stadium in Cornwall. It would be a great boost to tourism, the local economy and help encourage more people to play and watch sport. The current private sector proposal is very strong and we hope will be successful subject to planning permission. Planning decisions are a matter for the local Council which will report in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-07-20T16:19:52.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388907/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388907/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Sportsgrounds: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to paragraph 1.320 of the Summer Budget 2015, whether the Government plans to provide financial support for the building of a new stadium in Cornwall.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388908","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Department spent £5,550 on redesigning and rebuilding its blog platform in 2014. The blog is hosted on a shared platform and does not incur any additional on-going hosting and maintenance costs. All blog content and production is carried out in-house, which is managed jointly across the communications team with no additional spend.</p><p> </p><p>The breakdown below provides numbers of users to the DCMS blog since 28 July 2011. There is no data available before this date.</p><p> </p><p>These figures show that during 2012 and 2013 the DCMS blog played a key role in supporting a number of high-profile campaigns, including the London 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Games, resulting in a higher volume of blogs posted during this time which is reflected in a higher return in traffic. These figures also demonstrate how the blog is consistently meeting its objective to introduce a higher percentage of new audiences to our policies, the sectors we support and the voice of the people who champion them.</p><p> </p><p>· 2015 (to 17 July 2015): 6,984 users, of which 82.4% were new visitors and 17.6% were returning visitors</p><p>· 2014: 13,063 users, of which 82.6% were new visitors and 17.4% were returning</p><p>· 2013: 26,152 users of which 77.5% were new visitors and 22.5% were returning</p><p>· 2012: 38,575 users of which 74.8% were new visitors and 25.2% were returning</p><p>· 2011 (from 28 July): 9,667 of which 79.3% were new visitors and 20.7% were returning</p><p>Since the DCMS blog was launched in 2010, the Department has gone on to establish itself on a wider range of free social media channels targeted to its audiences and the evolving social media landscape.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-21T16:39:58.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388908/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388908/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department has spent on producing and maintaining dcmsblog.uk in each of the last five years; and how many unique visitors that blog has received in each such year.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388909","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-20","<p>Our consultation provides the opportunity for local newspapers to make the case for business rates relief. The consultation makes clear that, should we accept that there is a case for supporting local newspapers through the business rates system, any relief granted would be under state aid de minimis rules.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-20T13:08:06.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388909/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388909/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Local Press: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether he has sought legal advice on whether business rates relief for local newspapers complies with State Aid rules.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388910","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-17","<p>The sport strategy will be published later this year and we will inform the House in the normal course of business.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has today launched a five point plan on tourism to spread the benefits of one of our fastest growing sectors beyond the capital. A new inter ministerial group will be formed to coordinate and align action to boost tourism across Government. Copies of the five point plan are available in the House library.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-07-17T11:05:23.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388910/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388910/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","Sports and Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will publish tourism and sports strategies by 21 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388911","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-11-26","<p>Correspondence from the Secretary of State to the Scottish Government on BBC Charter Review has been published and can be foundon the Gov.uk website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bbc-charter-review-memoranda-of-understanding-with-the-devolved-administrations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bbc-charter-review-memoranda-of-understanding-with-the-devolved-administrations</a></p><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-26T17:16:30.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388911/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388911/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-09","BBC: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will publish his correspondence with the Scottish Government on BBC Charter renewal.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","6447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388912","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-14","<p>Following President Hollande's extremely generous offer in respect of awarding the Legion d'Honneur to veterans of the campaigns to liberate France, UK officials, both in London and at the Embassy in Paris, are engaging closely with their French colleagues in order that the process may be operated as quickly and as smoothly as possible.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-14T15:18:58.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388912/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388912/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Veterans: Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what representations he is making to the French government on awarding the Legion d'Honneur to D-Day veterans.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","6455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388913","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence takes seriously the psychological and physical health of all Armed Forces personnel. The RAF Reaper remotely piloted air systems force, alongside other frontline forces, has robust trauma risk management strategies in place to ensure this is continually monitored. Should psychological or physical care be required, the RAF medical services are fully engaged to provide the required level of support to the individual.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-07-14T15:24:24.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388913/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388913/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what psychological (a) assessment and (b) support his Department offers to the operators of UK Reaper Squadrons 39 and 13.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","6451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388914","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-17","<p>Three Tornado GR4 aircraft were deployed to Chad, from late August to mid October 2014 as part of the international effort to locate and retrieve the abducted Chibok schoolgirls in North East Nigeria. Up to ninety-one UK military personnel were in Chad supporting the Tornado aircraft, and those personnel had all returned to the UK by 17 October.</p><p>We learned a range of lessons from the Tornado GR4 deployment in Chad in 2014, not least in terms of the challenges associated with deploying fast jet aircraft to a new and austere location.</p><p>Since October, four UK military personnel have deployed to Chad in support of French counter-extremist activity in the region.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","6418 ; 6419","2015-07-17T13:21:22.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388914/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388914/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Chad: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether UK military personnel have been deployed in Chad since October 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","6420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388915","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD)'s Joint Doctrine Note (JDN) 2/11 &quot;The UK Approach to Unmanned Aircraft Systems&quot; was published on 30 March 2011. The principles contained within the note apply to systems and vehicles operating at sea and on land.</p><p>It is MOD policy that Joint Doctrine Notes remain valid for a limited period to inform future doctrine and concept publications. Work is under way to reflect and update the ideas contained within JDN 2/11 within new concepts and doctrine publications that are currently in production; at which point the note will be withdrawn. We expect this to be in the summer of 2016.</p><p>There are currently no plans to produce a new Joint Doctrine or Concept Note specifically on the UK approach to unmanned vehicles; however, the MOD reserves the right to do so in the future should the need arise.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-07-14T15:26:00.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388915/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388915/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Unmanned Air Vehicles and Unmanned Marine Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans to produce a new joint doctrinal note or joint concept note on the UK approach to unmanned vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","6480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388916","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) takes seriously the mental health of all members of the Armed Forces. The RAF Stress Management and Resilience Training Team has delivered stress awareness briefs to units operating unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), to give personnel awareness of the subject and make them aware of the wide range of assistance and treatment that is available.</p><p>While the particular stressors of their work are recognised, an assessment of the referral figures for MOD Departments of Community Mental Health from 2009-13 indicated that UAV pilots were no more likely to present with any form of mental health condition than the general Armed Forces population.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-07-14T15:25:14.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388916/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388916/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has undertaken or commissioned any assessment of the psychological effect of using unmanned air vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","6481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388917","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-17","<p>Three Tornado GR4 aircraft were deployed to Chad, from late August to mid October 2014 as part of the international effort to locate and retrieve the abducted Chibok schoolgirls in North East Nigeria. Up to ninety-one UK military personnel were in Chad supporting the Tornado aircraft, and those personnel had all returned to the UK by 17 October.</p><p>We learned a range of lessons from the Tornado GR4 deployment in Chad in 2014, not least in terms of the challenges associated with deploying fast jet aircraft to a new and austere location.</p><p>Since October, four UK military personnel have deployed to Chad in support of French counter-extremist activity in the region.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","6419 ; 6420","2015-07-17T13:21:22.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388917/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388917/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Chad: Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the lessons learnt were from the deployment of the RAF in Chad in 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","6418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388918","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-17","<p>Three Tornado GR4 aircraft were deployed to Chad, from late August to mid October 2014 as part of the international effort to locate and retrieve the abducted Chibok schoolgirls in North East Nigeria. Up to ninety-one UK military personnel were in Chad supporting the Tornado aircraft, and those personnel had all returned to the UK by 17 October.</p><p>We learned a range of lessons from the Tornado GR4 deployment in Chad in 2014, not least in terms of the challenges associated with deploying fast jet aircraft to a new and austere location.</p><p>Since October, four UK military personnel have deployed to Chad in support of French counter-extremist activity in the region.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","6418 ; 6420","2015-07-17T13:21:22.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388918/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388918/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-09","Chad: Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many aircraft were deployed in Chad in 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","6419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388919","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-15","<p>North Devon will continue to be served by search and rescue (SAR) helicopters operating from military bases at RMB Chivenor through to 1 October 2015 and RNAS Culdrose through to 1 January 2016. A new UK SAR helicopter service operating from new bases at Cardiff St Athan and Newquay Airport will take the place of SAR helicopter services currently operated out of RMB Chivenor and RNAS Culdrose. The start of these new services will coincide with the end of the military services at Chivenor and Culdrose, leaving no gap in SAR helicopter cover for south west England and south Wales. New helicopters offer improved operational capabilities and promise enhanced reliability.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-15T13:00:38.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388919/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388919/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Rescue Services: North Devon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that North Devon constituency is adequately covered by search and rescue services (a) in the summer and (b) at other times when such services are no longer based at RMB Chivenor.","false","Biography information for Peter Heaton-Jones","North Devon","Peter Heaton-Jones","6374"
